This paper proposes a new fair kernel regression method using fair feature embedding in kernel space. The paper focuses on mitigating unethical demographic biases in machine learning methods, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and security and privacy (cs.CR). Additionally, the proposed method involves feature processing, which is also relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
